column5: Anybody heading out to Bronte tonight? I am hoping after the rain the fish should start being active and hopefully bite. Good luck to all of you guys that are out there fishing!!
It's a cold front that's going to cause the rain....but you never know...they may be active.
The uglier the weather, the better the fishing for salmon at this time of year  It's going to be a zoo down there, avoiding like the plague myself  Tony

Winds are supposed to settle down tonight. I was hoping there wouldnt be that many people since the weather isn`t great and its really really windy. I am counting on rain to make fish more active. WE`ll see.
ya me and 4 friends are going to be there around 11 tonight fishing off the dark peir good luck everyone
I bet others are thinking the same  Good Luck Out There !
~~~I'll be down there on Sunday for a tourney, should be interesting
